data.meta_description: tradedvc on September 15, 2023: "Google.org, the charitable arm of Google, has launched the Digital Futures Project, which includes a $20 million fund to support AI-related research and public policy solutions. Founded by Google, this initiative aims to address the complexities and ethical considerations surrounding artificial intelligence (AI). It will provide grants to institutions globally, with inaugural recipients including prominent organizations such as the Aspen Institute, Brookings Institution, and MIT Work of the Future. Google emphasizes the importance of responsible AI development and governance as the AI community increasingly focuses on ethical practices and collaboration in the field.".
